 Minutes"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Probe Endpoint A\n\nGET https://service-a.example.com/healthz — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nNext: Combine Probe Results\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,250],"id":"8c391786-8d00-e345-b454-956fd04193b1","name":"Note: Probe Endpoint A"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Probe Endpoint B\n\nGET https://service-b.example.com/healthz — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nNext: Combine Probe Results\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,760],"id":"269380f5-c746-a1ce-c82d-e1ff4a121696","name":"Note: Probe Endpoint B"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Probe Endpoint C\n\nGET https://service-c.example.com/healthz — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nNext: Combine Probe Results\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,1270],"id":"b5d5f00d-0137-125a-6ac2-40698b6359c4","name":"Note: Probe Endpoint C"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Combine Probe Results\n\nRejoins 3 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: All Healthy?","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1290,520],"id":"fdf64322-f57a-755a-0434-2c37365dd1df","name":"Note: Combine Probe Results"},{"parameters":{"content":"### All Healthy?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ ($json.statusCode || 200) < 400 }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Uptime Metric · ②→ Already Alerted? (State Check)","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2262,520],"id":"58c480c3-78aa-d5a2-411a-48401070b828","name":"Note: All Healthy?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Uptime Metric\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Tag Pipeline Metadata · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2586,280],"id":"9b0a78d2-af22-6ba4-cfa8-04e5711b0485","name":"Note: Record Uptime Metric"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Already Alerted? (State Check)\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Page On-Call via Gmail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2910,880],"id":"f2e3a5c9-4713-c29e-4c33-13b7ee682a4d","name":"Note: Already Alerted? (State Check)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Page On-Call via Gmail\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3558,880],"id":"3704067b-f619-8f2a-cb20-f2a9699fc8de","name":"Note: Page On-Call via Gmail"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Tag Pipeline Metadata\n\nShapes the item: writes `pipeline`, `version`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Align Field Names","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"6a51670d-6632-33b7-c80b-251e86f162bd","name":"Note: Tag Pipeline Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Align Field Names\n\nNormalizes field names so every source feeds the same downstream schema.\n\nNext: Send Summary to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"6fdff950-7cb1-8ff0-b9e2-00761c4742a6","name":"Note: Align Field Names"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"229a717d-ecb4-c771-1f2e-fe242f20c6c7","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,1540],"id":"da957b05-14ff-c73c-03e2-a340ae564dd9","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,1540],"id":"5010ad94-6603-f9a1-1d96-d93e2513b4d8","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Watch spend with HTTP / REST API and Gmail with instant alerts\n\n**Pattern:** Threshold Monitoring · **Level:** Core · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nWatch spend with HTTP / REST API and Gmail with instant alerts. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual price alerts is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nEvery Few Minutes → Probe Endpoint A → Combine Probe Results → All Healthy? → Record Uptime Metric → Tag Pipeline Metadata → Align Field Names → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to threshold monitoring without manual effort\n- Anyone automating price alerts in finance\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"8964ec71-ff65-3462-53bd-77516adfac60","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-290],"id":"4a87f5ba-e8d0-a457-5e31-4d5a1319c63a","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-290],"id":"f3a0ea00-9946-49e3-cb37-d517f61b3546","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your price alerts process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-290],"id":"befa2eac-d79e-a744-73f5-e473da345dcc","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Every Few Minutes":{"main":[[{"node":"Probe Endpoint A","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Probe Endpoint B","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Probe Endpoint C","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Probe Endpoint A":{"main":[[{"node":"Combine Probe Results","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Probe Endpoint B":{"main":[[{"node":"Combine Probe Results","type":"main","index":1}]]},"Probe Endpoint C":{"main":[[{"node":"Combine Probe Results","type":"main","index":2}]]},"Combine Probe Results":{"main":[[{"node":"All Healthy?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"All Healthy?":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Uptime Metric","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Already Alerted? (State Check)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Already Alerted? (State Check)":{"main":[[{"node":"Page On-Call via Gmail","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Uptime Metric":{"main":[[{"node":"Tag Pipeline Metadata","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Tag Pipeline Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Align Field Names","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Align Field Names":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Page On-Call via Gmail":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"8b13aa2f-5225-4c68-8b69-4781ca8c7e5b","id":"FDX08882"}